#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="sn7.8"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn7.8:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 7 "
msgstr "Linked Discourses 7 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn7.8:0.2"
msgid "1. Arahantavagga "
msgstr "1. The Perfected Ones "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "sn7.8:0.3"
msgid "8. Aggikasutta "
msgstr "8. With Bhāradvāja the Fire-Worshipper "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: sc1
msgctxt "sn7.8:1.1"
msgid "Ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā rājagahe viharati veḷuvane kalandakanivāpe. "
msgstr "At one time the Buddha was staying near Rājagaha, in the Bamboo Grove, the squirrels’ feeding ground. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn7.8:1.2"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena aggikabhāradvājassa brāhmaṇassa sappinā pāyaso sannihito hoti: "
msgstr "Now at that time ghee and milk-rice had been set out for the brahmin Bhāradvāja the Fire-Worshipper, who thought, "

msgctxt "sn7.8:1.3"
msgid "“aggiṃ juhissāmi, aggihuttaṃ paricarissāmī”ti. "
msgstr "“I will serve the sacred flame! I will perform the fire sacrifice!” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc2
msgctxt "sn7.8:2.1"
msgid "Atha kho bhagavā pubbaṇhasamayaṃ nivāsetvā pattacīvaramādāya rājagahaṃ piṇḍāya pāvisi. "
msgstr "Then the Buddha robed up in the morning and, taking his bowl and robe, entered Rājagaha for alms. "

msgctxt "sn7.8:2.2"
msgid "Rājagahe sapadānaṃ piṇḍāya caramāno yena aggikabhāradvājassa brāhmaṇassa nivesanaṃ tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā ekamantaṃ aṭṭhāsi. "
msgstr "Wandering indiscriminately for alms-food in Rājagaha, he approached Bhāradvāja the Fire-Worshiper’s house and stood to one side. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn7.8:2.3"
msgid "Addasā kho aggikabhāradvājo brāhmaṇo bhagavantaṃ piṇḍāya ṭhitaṃ. "
msgstr "Bhāradvāja the Fire-Worshipper saw him standing for alms "

msgctxt "sn7.8:2.4"
msgid "Disvāna bhagavantaṃ gāthāya ajjhabhāsi: "
msgstr "and addressed him in verse: "

#. HTML: </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. REF: pts2ed1.357, sc3
msgctxt "sn7.8:3.1"
msgid "“Tīhi vijjāhi sampanno, "
msgstr "“One who’s accomplished in the three knowledges, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn7.8:3.2"
msgid "jātimā sutavā bahū; "
msgstr "of good lineage and ample learning, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn7.8:3.3"
msgid "Vijjācaraṇasampanno, "
msgstr "accomplished in knowledge and conduct "

# NOTE: somaṁ is, sadly, so imaṁ, not a reference to soma.
#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn7.8:3.4"
msgid "somaṃ bhuñjeyya pāyasan”ti. "
msgstr "may enjoy this milk-rice.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc4
msgctxt "sn7.8:4.1"
msgid "“Bahumpi palapaṃ jappaṃ, "
msgstr "“Even one who mutters many invocations "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn7.8:4.2"
msgid "na jaccā hoti brāhmaṇo; "
msgstr "is no brahmin by birth "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn7.8:4.3"
msgid "Antokasambu saṅkiliṭṭho, "
msgstr "if they’re filthy and corrupt within, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn7.8:4.4"
msgid "kuhanāparivārito. "
msgstr "with a following gained by fraud. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts1ed1.167, sc5
msgctxt "sn7.8:5.1"
msgid "Pubbenivāsaṃ yo vedī, "
msgstr "But one who knows their past lives, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn7.8:5.2"
msgid "saggāpāyañca passati; "
msgstr "and sees heaven and places of loss, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn7.8:5.3"
msgid "Atho jātikkhayaṃ patto, "
msgstr "and has attained the ending of rebirth, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn7.8:5.4"
msgid "abhiññāvosito muni. "
msgstr "that sage has perfect insight. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc6
msgctxt "sn7.8:6.1"
msgid "Etāhi tīhi vijjāhi, "
msgstr "Because of these three knowledges "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn7.8:6.2"
msgid "tevijjo hoti brāhmaṇo; "
msgstr "a brahmin is a master of the three knowledges. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn7.8:6.3"
msgid "Vijjācaraṇasampanno, "
msgstr "Accomplished in knowledge and conduct, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn7.8:6.4"
msgid "somaṃ bhuñjeyya pāyasan”ti. "
msgstr "they may enjoy this milk-rice.” "

#. HTML: </p></blockquote><p>
#. REF: pts2ed1.358, sc7
msgctxt "sn7.8:7.1"
msgid "“Bhuñjatu bhavaṃ gotamo. "
msgstr "“Eat, Master Gotama! "

msgctxt "sn7.8:7.2"
msgid "Brāhmaṇo bhavan”ti. "
msgstr "you are truly a brahmin.” "

# NOTE: https://discourse.suttacentral.net/t/on-chanting-and-enchanting/3376
#. HTML: </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. REF: sc8
msgctxt "sn7.8:8.1"
msgid "“Gāthābhigītaṃ me abhojaneyyaṃ, "
msgstr "“Food enchanted by a spell isn’t fit for me to eat. "

# NOTE: Here sampassata comes close in sense to “empiricist, scientist, rationalist”
#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn7.8:8.2"
msgid "Sampassataṃ brāhmaṇa nesa dhammo; "
msgstr "That’s not the way of those who see, brahmin. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn7.8:8.3"
msgid "Gāthābhigītaṃ panudanti buddhā, "
msgstr "The Buddhas reject things enchanted with spells. "

# NOTE: Norman has “doctrine” for Dhamma here, which doesn’t make sense. BB’s “principle” is preferable. I think the sense of the line is “that’s how we live because we’re in a rational universe.” I would compare the locative absolute here with the common ditthevadhamme, i.e. in apparent, empirical existence.
#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn7.8:8.4"
msgid "Dhamme sati brāhmaṇa vuttiresā. "
msgstr "Since nature is real, brahmin, that’s how they live. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc9
msgctxt "sn7.8:9.1"
msgid "Aññena ca kevalinaṃ mahesiṃ, "
msgstr "Serve with other food and drink "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn7.8:9.2"
msgid "Khīṇāsavaṃ kukkuccavūpasantaṃ; "
msgstr "the consummate one, the great hermit, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn7.8:9.3"
msgid "Annena pānena upaṭṭhahassu, "
msgstr "with defilements ended and remorse stilled. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn7.8:9.4"
msgid "Khettañhi taṃ puññapekkhassa hotī”ti. "
msgstr "For he is the field for the seeker of merit.” "

#. HTML: </p></blockquote><p>
#. REF: sc10
msgctxt "sn7.8:10.1"
msgid "Evaṃ vutte, aggikabhāradvājo brāhmaṇo bhagavantaṃ etadavoca: "
msgstr "When he had spoken, the brahmin Bhāradvāja the Fire-Worshipper said to the Buddha, "

msgctxt "sn7.8:10.2"
msgid "“abhikkantaṃ, bho gotama … pe … "
msgstr "“Excellent, Master Gotama! …” … "

msgctxt "sn7.8:10.3"
msgid "aññataro ca panāyasmā aggikabhāradvājo arahataṃ ahosīti. "
msgstr "And Venerable Bhāradvāja the Fire-Worshipper became one of the perfected."

#. HTML: </p></article></section></body></html>
